WEBVTT

00:05:54.720 --> 00:06:00.720
Imagine awarding 100 Pulitzer Prizes
to one author for the same book.

00:06:00.744 --> 00:06:02.021
(Murmurs)

00:06:02.735 --> 00:06:04.695
It doesn't have to be this way.

00:06:04.719 --> 00:06:07.776
We can create a modern patent system

00:06:07.800 --> 00:06:11.219
to meet the needs
of a 21st-century society.

00:06:11.243 --> 00:06:12.442
And to do that,

00:06:12.466 --> 00:06:15.823
we need to reimagine the patent system
to serve the public,

00:06:15.847 --> 00:06:17.934
not just corporations.

00:06:18.736 --> 00:06:20.003
So how do we do it?

00:06:20.752 --> 00:06:22.172
Five reforms.

00:06:22.633 --> 00:06:26.332
First, we need to stop
handing out so many patents.

00:06:27.077 --> 00:06:29.181
Back under the Kennedy administration,

00:06:29.205 --> 00:06:32.753
in an effort to curb rising drug costs,